From 522050ee16d2d34a7df5ef620b08a07410e44d45 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dhanavandhana Kannan <quic_dhanavan1@quicinc.com>
Date: Mon, 3 Mar 2025 11:34:00 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:wpa_supplicant: Fix removed BSS not found
 during successive link removals

Currently when the first primary link is removed via dynamic link
removal, wpa_flush_bss_by_age() eliminates inactive BSS from the
supplicant scan results after a certain period. When the second
primary link is subsequently removed, the supplicant sends a
deauthentication message because the BSS of the first removed primary
link is no longer found in the scan results. This occurs when the
requested links during association are checked for their presence in
the scan results within the wpa_sm_set_ml_info() function during link
removal.

To fix this, ensure that if a removed BSS is not present in the scan
results due to the flush, the BSS not found failure is skipped by
verifying that the removed BSS does not belong to valid links.

Patch-dependency: r32-006-Hostapd-Handle-EVENT_RX_MGMT-event-for-link-
                  reconfig.patch
Patch-work: None

Signed-off-by: Dhanavandhana Kannan <quic_dhanavan1@quicinc.com>
---
 src/rsn_supp/wpa.c      | 2 ++
 wpa_supplicant/events.c | 2 ++
 2 files changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/rsn_supp/wpa.c b/src/rsn_supp/wpa.c
index ebbd0c9..0f6d1d1 100644
--- a/src/rsn_supp/wpa.c
+++ b/src/rsn_supp/wpa.c
@@ -4714,6 +4714,8 @@ int wpa_sm_set_mlo_params(struct wpa_sm *sm, const struct wpa_sm_mlo *mlo)
 		if (sm->mlo.req_links & BIT(i)) {
 			if (!mlo->links[i].ap_rsne ||
 			    mlo->links[i].ap_rsne_len == 0) {
+				if (!(sm->mlo.valid_links & BIT(i)))
+					continue;
 				wpa_dbg(sm->ctx->msg_ctx, MSG_INFO,
 					"RSN: No RSNE for AP MLO link %d with BSSID "
 					MACSTR,
diff --git a/wpa_supplicant/events.c b/wpa_supplicant/events.c
index b6d8e48..ca415c4 100644
--- a/wpa_supplicant/events.c
+++ b/wpa_supplicant/events.c
@@ -4213,6 +4213,8 @@ static int wpa_sm_set_ml_info(struct wpa_supplicant *wpa_s)
 
 		bss = wpa_supplicant_get_new_bss(wpa_s, drv_mlo.links[i].bssid);
 		if (!bss) {
+			if (!(wpa_mlo.valid_links & BIT(i)))
+				continue;
 			wpa_dbg(wpa_s, MSG_INFO,
 				"Failed to get MLO link %d BSS", i);
 			return -1;
-- 
